    @*BACKGROUND*@
    <div id="background" class="relpos container container-md mt-lg-5">
        <h2>Background</h2>
        <p style="padding-top: 2%">
            So we were tasked with creating a new church management operations system, ChurchPoint, that
            would be a operational efficenty system that could service different types of church and regardless of size. This system would
            include specific functions that the client would like that other church management systems could not offer.
        </p>
    </div>

    <hr /> 

    @*PROBLEM*@
    <div id="problem" class="relpos container mt-lg-5">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-sm">
                <h4 style="text-align: center";>The Problem </h4>
                    <ol style="text-align: left;">
                        <li>The current church managment systems are entirely dependent on the size and function the church wants to perform.</li>
                        <li>Current church management systems targeted only specific or general functions of a church, which may not be sutiable in a particular needs of a church.</li>
                    </ol>
            </div>

            <div class="col-sm">
            <h4 style="text-align: center";>The Proposed Solution</h4>
            <p style="text-align: center;"padding-top: 2%">
                Is to create a church management system that be a process-driven (based on discipleship church) software that contains 
                a service-oriented information system that was robust. This system would be architected to be extensible, flexible
                security-compliant, and adaptable to any church environment no matter the size of the church.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <hr />

    @*HIGHLIGHTS*@
    <div id="highlights" class="relpos container mt-lg-5">
        <h2>Highlights</h2>
        <h4 style="padding-top: 3%">Social & Event Engagement</h4>
        <p style="padding-top: 2%">Inclusive church information can be found within the website that will display social engagements as well as allow for events to be created and handled. </p>
        <h4 style="padding-top: 3%">Membership Services</h4>
        <p style="padding-top: 2%">Track the attendance of Members, visitors, and be able to display the data within a time period.</p>
        <h4 style="padding-top: 3%">Resource Management</h4>
        <p style="padding-top: 2%">Consists of all the necesarry application and division of powers that is needed within a business. (HR, Finance and Treasury, Staff, Volunteers, Inventory, etc.)</p>
        <h4 style="padding-top: 3%">Ministry Services</h4>
        <p style="padding-top: 2%">Tailored specifically for a church management software, these features will include Prayrer, Discipleship, Koinonia, Praise & Worship, Evangalism, etc.</p>
    </div>

    <hr />

    @*SCOPE*@
    <div class="container mt-lg-5">
        <h2 id="scope">Scope</h2>
        <p style="padding-top: 2%">
            Churchpoint will allow user to manage single or multiple churches through the implementation of the application
            where all of the necessary things to build a successful church will be located anywhere that there is access to a webpage.
        </p>
    </div>

